These do make me sleepy, and I do have strange and memorable dreams. I‚Äôve always been suspect of melatonin and never found it to work for me. But this does the trick. review_text: I got these to help me when I was having trouble falling or staying asleep. I am 28, generally healthy, rarely use medication, have never taken a sleeping aid before. This year was my first time dipping into taking melatonin. I decided to take 1 gummy to see how that went (serving size is 2 gummies). I will only take 2 gummies if I feel extra awake and I need to sleep ASAP. I always allow myself at least 6 hours of sleep when taking it. This has been my experience over this past year: Pros: - *usually* half an hour after taking this, I will start to feel sleepy and extra comfortable in my bed, which helps me drift off to sleep. - no next-day grogginess if used on a need-only basis for no more than 2-3 days in a row (usually no more than a few or couple times a month). - the gummies are tasty, IMO Cons: - I may experience next-day grogginess or weird dreams if I use this too many days in a row (usually after 4+ days of consecutive use). - This doesn‚Äôt necessarily always guarantee me a great quality of sleep, but I think that‚Äôs more due to other factors (i.e. whatever my state of anxiety is at the time, very disruptive sleeping patterns) and it is still better than it would have been without it, IMO. Overall, I love this product. I work as a teacher aid and I have the same breaks that my students do, so this helps me get my schedule back on track after breaks. I wish I had tried this in high school and college, I had a harder time sleeping then!! Also helps because I have a hard time falling asleep when I have a big day ahead. I think it‚Äôs totally worth trying and seeing if this works for you. I feel like this has a short learning curve to see what dosage and frequency works for you.
